<edge_computing_security_guide>
<title>EDGE COMPUTING SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Edge computing security covers Cloudflare Workers, Vercel Edge Functions, Deno Deploy, and Lambda@Edge. Testing focuses on edge-specific vulnerabilities, KV store security, and geographic bypass.</critical>

<scope>
- Cloudflare Workers security
- Vercel Edge Functions
- Deno Deploy testing
- AWS Lambda@Edge
- Edge-specific vulnerabilities
- KV store security
- Geographic bypass
</scope>

<cloudflare_workers>
{% raw %}
# Workers security:
# Check for exposed secrets:
env.API_KEY

# Test KV store access:
await NAMESPACE.get('key')

# SSRF via fetch():
await fetch(userInput)
{% endraw %}
</cloudflare_workers>

<edge_bypass>
{% raw %}
# Geographic restrictions bypass:
# Use VPN/proxy in allowed region

# Edge cache bypass:
# Cache-Control: no-cache
# Pragma: no-cache
{% endraw %}
</edge_bypass>

<remember>Edge security: Check Workers for secret exposure, test KV store permissions, validate fetch() SSRF protection, attempt geographic bypass.</remember>
</edge_computing_security_guide>
